# Cloudflare Workers (Static Assets) custom response headers.
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/static-assets/headers/
#
# Applies to responses served directly by Static Assets: the document (index.html) and the bundled
# JS / CSS / font assets — i.e. exactly what CSP and frame-ancestors govern.
#
# IMPORTANT: these headers do NOT apply to responses generated by the Worker (worker/index.ts),
# even when the request URL matches a rule here. /config.js is Worker-generated (run_worker_first),
# so its one security-relevant header (nosniff) is set in worker/config-response.ts, not here.
#
# This file ships UNCHANGED to dev/uat/prod (build-once-promote), so the CSP below is identical
# across all three envs. `connect-src` is 'self' today because API_BASE_URL / WS_URL are empty;
# this is the line where exchange wss:// origins will go. Once those differ per env, the CSP must
# move into the Worker (built from env vars, like /config.js). See docs/security-headers-setup.md.

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000
